  "articleSummary": "The article is a brief tutorial aimed at system administrators and MongoDB users on Debian‑based systems who encounter the warning “/sys/kernel/mm/transparent_hugepage/defrag is ‘always’.” It explains that MongoDB recommends disabling Transparent Huge Pages (THP) to avoid performance degradation, and provides a quick, ready‑to‑run set of shell commands that download a pre‑written init script, make it executable, and register it to start at boot. The piece references the official MongoDB documentation for deeper context, and its tone is pragmatic and instructional rather than argumentative or opinionated.",
